
HTML :
<button id="toggleBtn">Toggle Content</button> → Button to show/hide content
<div id="content">Hidden Text</div> → Content to be toggled

CSS :
display: none; → Initially hides content
transition: 0.3s ease-in-out; → Smooth animation
.active { display: block; } → Shows content when active

JavaScript :
document.getElementById("toggleBtn") → Selects the button
classList.toggle("active") → Adds or removes the active class
onclick → Detects button click
